H1> What is BBCode?

P> BBCode is a safe, lightweight markup that compiles to HTML. It lets your users (and admins) format text without the security risks of accepting raw HTML.

Q> What's BBCode?
A> A BBCode is a shortcut for an HTML tag. For example typing [b]&#91;b]I am bold![&#91;/b][/b] in any admin textbox will render as [b]I am bold![/b] on the front-end.

Q> But what's it for?
A> It saves time and prevents broken markup. You can still use plain HTML in admin textareas, but BBCode is faster to type and is consistently sanitised by the parser.

H1> Tips and quirks

Q> When I click a BBCode button it inserts the tag at the end of my text, not at the cursor – why?
A> An old Internet Explorer bug could crash the editor when injecting at the cursor position. For maximum compatibility e107 still appends BBCode at the end of the textarea.

Q> Which BBCodes can I use?
A> Hover over any of the BBCode buttons – a small tooltip shows what each one does. You can also use [b]&#91;url][/b], [b]&#91;email][/b], [b]&#91;img][/b], [b]&#91;list][/b] and many more. Bare URLs and email addresses are auto-linked.

TIP> You can extend the available BBCodes by adding files to `e107_core/bbcodes/` (or via plugins). See `e107_handlers/bbcode_handler.php` for the API.
